data.description: This property has an assumable VA loan  at 4.125% with a balance of $223,221.46.  Any qualified buyer could assume this loan and this very low rate.   Nestled in the Carver/Langston neighborhood, this classic condo exudes a seamless blend of 1940s architecture with contemporary functionality. With its origins tracing back to 1941, the property maintains its vintage walk-up allure, highlighted by the external brick facade.  Spanning a comfortable 800 square feet, this elegant dwelling boasts two spacious bedrooms complemented by a full bathroom and an additional half bath, ensuring ease and convenience for its inhabitants. Bask in the warmth of its hardwood flooring, evoking an ambiance of comfort. For those who drive, the added benefit of a dedicated parking space ensures seamless accessibility.  Just steps away from the expansive nature of the National Arboretum, the surrounding community is a testament to refined urban living. For those who prefer a hands-on approach to amenities, the property's proximity to local establishments is a boon. You are just a short walk from all your favorite H Street NE retail outlets and your favorite restaurants in Union Market.  Invitingly priced and conveniently positioned, this condo is more than just a dwelling – it is an opportunity to own in the heart of DC. Take a moment to look closely at this condo before it is gone.
